1 (i) only natural gas energy and energy storage;
2 (ii) only nuclear energy and energy storage; and
3 (iii) only offshore wind energy and energy storage;
4 (4) identify the costs for natural gas, nuclear, and offshore wind if energy
5 storage is available to offset reliability and intermittency issues; and
6 (5) include recommended policy changes to support the development of the
7 energy sources with the lowest costs and greatest benefits to the ratepayers of the State.
8 (c) On or before December 1, 2026, the Public Service Commission shall report its
9 findings and recommendations to the Senate Committee on Education, Energy, and the
10 Environment and the House Economic Matters Committee, in accordance with § 2–1257 of
11 the State Government Article.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
13 October 1, 2025.

